      "message": "Oh, hmm.  This was intended to enable the attribute only for Clang, with other compilers ignoring unknown attributes.  If we\u0027re going to enable it for both Clang and GCC, let\u0027s use SK_ATTRIBUTE(no_sanitize(...)).  That\u0027s defined in SkTypes.h as\n\n#if !defined(SK_ATTRIBUTE)\n#  if defined(__clang__) || defined(__GNUC__)\n#    define SK_ATTRIBUTE(attr) __attribute__((attr))\n#  else\n#    define SK_ATTRIBUTE(attr)\n#  endif\n#endif",
